##The authors of 12 cities are simultaneously documenting | Sandwich China Sketch 01

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

In February, Sandwich launched "China Sketch" , which aims to capture the moment across China in the plainest and most moving manner possible. The cities that have started to be recorded are Ningbo, Baise, Xianyang, Shanghai, Hong Kong, Shantou, Jinan, Yantai, Nanjing, Suzhou, Chongqing, Ensch..

This particular moment, in China's tens of millions of cities and villages, how the face of life was changed overnight, if we can leave a little record, is not to forget, not to forget.

The Observer from the tower
By Chenchu
Coordinates: Ningbo, Zhejiang

When I started working, I moved to the top floor of an old apartment building in a busy part of town.

How can I describe where I live? The next floor is the intersection of line 1 and Line 2. If you look out of the room, on the left is the drum tower, on the right is the Tianyi Square, behind is the city God temple, in front is the former site of the municipal government, the present site of the district government. It was in this prime location that I got into the habit of looking out the window of the 26th floor every day, at the traffic below, at the mountains in the distance.

In the middle of Ningbo, as seen from my room. In the lower right corner of the screen is the Old City government office building, and in the upper left corner is the Ningbo Second Hospital, the designated hospital for pneumonia.

The control of the epidemic in Ningbo has probably been tightened since the Spring Festival. Private cars are fewer than in previous Chinese New Year, less than every traffic light, the intersection of the queue is only two or three cars. At first, there were plenty of buses running on time. Because the road is clear, actually feel that the frequency of the bus is even higher than usual. Then one day, all the subway lines stopped, and the buses were spaced an hour apart. Bike-sharing and citizen cycling have long been neglected. The street was almost silent after nine o'clock in the evening.

Ningbo Tianyi Square, the old Praça do Comércio in a busy downtown area.
At the height of the outbreak, the midday hours were empty.

Yao Hang Street, next to Tianyi Square, almost no cars.
At the end of the road is a nearly 100-year-old bridge.

Instead of roads filled with cars and buses, there are just a few delivery boys, taxis, and ambulances that sometimes pull alarms and sometimes don't. Originally riding a battery car is very free and easy little brothers, after dark simply rode on the fast lane, whizzing across the intersection to their destination, people worry about their safety. Seeing the taxi go by, I can't help thinking, how many orders can they get today? There's not a lot of people on the road. If a passing taxi doesn't have a little green light on, they will be happy for them for a little while: But finally received customers!

When it comes to ambulances, there's a lot of them. Looking ahead from the intersection of the four branches downstairs, the Second Hospital of Ningbo is located on the left-hand side. It is a designated hospital for patients. The ambulances on the empty streets were easy to spot, though they seemed to pass much of the time in silence, almost impassive. Were they carrying the wounded or the ordinary? The distance from the building to the ground allowed me to observe the motionless ambulances as if they were a painting.

Between the second courtyard and the apartment building where I live, there is a large Zhongshan Square, which can be seen clearly from the window. When I was a kid, I lived in the back of Zhongshan Square, which is now surrounded by a historic preservation block in the city that has yet to be renovated. These days, I often recall what Zhongshan Square looked like before the outbreak began. Because there is a huge open area, and in the city center, many residents will usually ride electric bicycle, from afternoon to night in the square ballroom dancing, disco, break dancing and other dance feel very old. On one occasion, I watched a video of someone recording the dance moves of Zhongshan Square's break dancing king. It's just that there was a sense of excitement that was suddenly sucked away by a powerful vacuum cleaner. At night, the landscape lights on the ground are still on. Are They stand-ins for these dancers? Why aren't they talking?

The third confirmed case was a noodle shop owner
Recorded by: Rabbit Rain
COORDINATES: Guangxi, Baise

This is Baise, a small city on the southwestern border of Guangxi. It is geographically close to Southeast Asia and shares a border with Vietnam. The terrain is mainly mountainous and hilly, with few plains. Motorbikes and electric cars are the most popular way to get around. It is a special habit of people to go to the vegetable market while riding an electric bicycle.

With the announcement of the prevention and control of new pneumonia in the Youjiang district of Baise City, the food service industry and Itinerant Street vendors in the city of Baise have been completely banned.

A spacious back alley is rare in Dongfeng vegetable market

Near the fish stall at Dongfeng vegetable market

It was the longest frozen Spring Festival in Baise City for more than 20 years, both physically and psychologically. With the third confirmed case being a noodle shop owner, stalls across the city of Baise have been shut down, and it is hard to see a scene like that again as electric cars and cars pile up in waves in front of the shop, bowl after bowl of hot rice noodles opened people's hopes for a new day. And now, the closed powder shop shutter door and behind the boss, like a sigh out of a special period of helplessness in the town.

In one night, in the countryside, there are no fresh vegetables, seedlings and fruits, no local chickens, no local ducks, no local goods, no river fish, no shrimp, no rice snail, no fresh steamed glutinous rice rolls made by craftsmen from Xiangqing Alley near the city of Taicai

Dongfeng Vegetable Market Poultry vendors sporadic business

Local snack collective off-line, food bigger than days of small town people began a penance-like life. You can't pick and choose, you can't shop around, you can't haggle with vendors, you can't tell them what to do. This slow pace, small life of the people in the town, simply lost the fun of shopping, the spirit! The outbreak of the epidemic has made it psychologically difficult for both the buyer and the seller to take care of their lives outside the transaction. Wearing a mask, it has also become more difficult to read the subtle expressions between the buyer and the seller, thus reducing the fun of the game.

Everyone is in a hurry, mechanically to complete the task of buying food, but also to endure limited purchase, endure queuing, endure distribution..

Want to pass the mouth addiction, all rely on their own craft! Some Astute self-employed, breeders, growers, and craftsmen have gathered around to keep warm, and have formed various social groups. With the help of short video, Vlog, Wechat Dragon and other forms, wind and fire have started online marketing. The local snack has completed the state renewal and the circulation, reappears in a new form in the small town people field of vision.

Everyone's avoiding meeting anyone
REPORTER: Sanmang
COORDINATES: Xianyang, Shaanxi

This small town has no shortage of living materials, supermarket management strict. Take the elevator down, secretly cough, but also led to the opposite upward elevator on a pair of white eyes, white hair dazzling hat. Subtext in the eyes.

There weren't many people in the supermarket, but they were all trying to avoid meeting anyone and enjoying the pungent smell of disinfectant on the shelves. Of course, no one had time to enjoy it. It's not a romantic moment, and it's hard to capture the joy in the pain.

The normally bustling snack area is now empty.

The brain is: "Salt and vinegar, seasoning area! Roll paper and paper, yes, close to the stationery area! Vegetables and fruit last to buy, now, people must be crowded in that area... " the ultimate rational calculation of the route and time, to maintain the security alone.

But as long as you go deep into the fruit and vegetable area, you can't avoid being caught between the left and the right, forcing everyone to get a head start and take the shopping cart. The old man who had been chosen sugar orange in front took a shortcut, but he was still in the crevice, waiting for help, alert and with his mouth shut. The voice in my head said again, "why don't I wear gloves... what's the matter... are these people from around here... I want to cough... can't... people are afraid... "

If it was just a line in someone's head, it wouldn't be so loud. The same fears hanging in the air. Knowing the state of a character in a novel depends on what he says and what he is doing. Looking at the old man again, she had picked up the oranges in her hand as fast as she could. They were all full of juice. With the mask on, what's the line she can't say? Is that enough to hide vulnerability? Like the "dusk is late night" , "less hardship, no fear today, " such lines, she went out in front of the mirror silently read, but now it is a sonorous towards me, grabbed me, melt uneasy. But inadvertently, already from the old man to hold hold the concentration of the orange to catch a secret word into the pocket, encourage their own step.

With the price tag on, the old man pushed away all kinds of fruits and vegetables, different brands of rice flour oil, and went straight to the plate of eggs. The road was clear. I exchanged glances with the meter reader and put a price tag on the tomato. Whisper thank you, he did not hear, but stretched out his hand, also "tomorrow will be better" the secret word to him.

Old People always look at the fate, epiphany with time layer upon layer, layer upon layer of light and dense, can not be said with others. But the disease had to cut open the heart with a knife to prove the depth of this great enlightenment, and the city's elderly were not stingy with wisdom. Running around the supermarket, it's their front line against the plague, the sweet salt that guards the town. It was a romantic moment in a small town, and early in the morning the idea of making the best of a bad situation arose.

What was your city like before the outbreak in 50 words?

Recorded by: Rabbit Rain
COORDINATES: Baise, Guangxi
I live in a small city on the 18th line of China's southwest frontier, with Southeast Asian characteristics. The mountainous region is close to the Tropic of Cancer, and most of the locals are lean, dark and yellow. During the outbreak, the temperature in the small town continued to drop, people put on heavy cotton clothes, put on white masks, due to the few confirmed cases, people look like heart fat, skin color with mask light, white several degrees.
Reporter: Song Rui
Coordinates: Ensch, Hubei
As a tourist city, it is normal to be noisy and noisy day and night. In addition to the ever crowded scenic spot, the bean skin shop and slag shop roadside food stalls and Tujia restaurant are the main force, and when night falls, massage parlors light up red and green signs, the streets and alleys are always a battlefield for businessmen. Every time we go home, we will go to eat bean skin too early, the same day cooked bean skin smooth, green pepper with just out of the WOK of gas, add a little hot oil is the perfect breakfast, eat go out to meet acquaintances again.
REPORTER: Tsurugi
COORDINATES: Suzhou
She was beautiful, a combination of modernity and classicality, full of energy and elegance. Her Rhythm is fast, whether on weekdays or weekends, morning and evening rush hour, the subway is always crowded out of the level of the big city. Business districts such as Guanqian Street and central Suzhou are popular with young people, who line up at the entrance of the hotel every day. Pishi Street, fenmen and other old blocks is the world of the elderly, Suzhou aunt even with hawkers bargain, Go-on still soft waxy good-sounding. It's a very inclusive city, with more than 10 million residents. Before the outbreak of panic, the city, and its people, led an orderly Soviet life.
Written by Li Er-ma
COORDINATES: Hong Kong
Hong Kong is a city of great vitality and resilience, people say. After the turmoil of the last six months, I believe. For more than six months, Hong Kong has been under a cacophony of alarms and noises before the alert sounded. There were a lot of Saturday nights... When you could see the smoke on the TV... and the wolves of Mancheng District were borrowing it. When the day dawned again, to everyone's surprise, the MTR had swept up all the broken glass on the ground and began to pick up a truck full of suits and shoes to go back to work.

What did you do last time you were out?

Written by: Wang Mumu
Coordinates: Heze, Shandong
On the 11th day of the first lunar month, my husband and I secretly went back to my mother's house, because all the roads in and out of the villages were blocked and cars could not get in and out. I had to ride my moped around the dirt road. The Path was bumpy and pitted, and it nearly knocked everything out of my stomach. It was a five-minute drive, but we had to walk around for almost half an hour.
REPORTER: Big Cake
COORDINATES: Chongqing
Six, the night before the lockdown, me and my sister. "Do you want to go out to see what it's like? " My sister is a child, big New Year's Day ten days did not go on the street, where know those heart-wrenching story, painful tears, only two eyes straight to me. We were out on the street, alone. The banks of the river that flows through the town are covered with golden lanterns. They are quietly reflected in the river. We look down at the lanterns. A small boat is leaning on the bank. The lanterns are like stars in the sky. I wonder how many people can see it.

She was beautiful, a combination of modernity and classicality, full of energy and elegance. Her Rhythm is fast, whether on weekdays or weekends, morning and evening rush hour, the subway is always crowded out of the level of the big city. Business districts such as Guanqian Street and central Suzhou are popular with young people, who line up at the entrance of the hotel every day. Pishi Street, fenmen and other old blocks is the world of the elderly, Suzhou aunt even with hawkers bargain, Go-on still soft waxy good-sounding. It's a very inclusive city, with more than 10 million residents. Before the outbreak of panic, the city, and its people, led an orderly Soviet life.
Written by Li Er-ma
COORDINATES: Hong Kong
Hong Kong is a city of great vitality and resilience, people say. After the turmoil of the last six months, I believe. For more than six months, Hong Kong has been under a cacophony of alarms and noises before the alert sounded. There were a lot of Saturday nights... When you could see the smoke on the TV... and the wolves of Mancheng District were borrowing it. When the day dawned again, to everyone's surprise, the MTR had swept up all the broken glass on the ground and began to pick up a truck full of suits and shoes to go back to work.

What did you do last time you were out?

Written by: Wang Mumu
Coordinates: Heze, Shandong
On the 11th day of the first lunar month, my husband and I secretly went back to my mother's house, because all the roads in and out of the villages were blocked and cars could not get in and out. I had to ride my moped around the dirt road. The Path was bumpy and pitted, and it nearly knocked everything out of my stomach. It was a five-minute drive, but we had to walk around for almost half an hour.
REPORTER: Big Cake
COORDINATES: Chongqing
Six, the night before the lockdown, me and my sister. "Do you want to go out to see what it's like? " My sister is a child, big New Year's Day ten days did not go on the street, where know those heart-wrenching story, painful tears, only two eyes straight to me. We were out on the street, alone. The banks of the river that flows through the town are covered with golden lanterns. They are quietly reflected in the river. We look down at the lanterns. A small boat is leaning on the bank. The lanterns are like stars in the sky. I wonder how many people can see it.

The brain is: "Salt and vinegar, seasoning area! Roll paper and paper, yes, close to the stationery area! Vegetables and fruit last to buy, now, people must be crowded in that area... " the ultimate rational calculation of the route and time, to maintain the security alone.

But as long as you go deep into the fruit and vegetable area, you can't avoid being caught between the left and the right, forcing everyone to get a head start and take the shopping cart. The old man who had been chosen sugar orange in front took a shortcut, but he was still in the crevice, waiting for help, alert and with his mouth shut. The voice in my head said again, "why don't I wear gloves... what's the matter... are these people from around here... I want to cough... can't... people are afraid... "

If it was just a line in someone's head, it wouldn't be so loud. The same fears hanging in the air. Knowing the state of a character in a novel depends on what he says and what he is doing. Looking at the old man again, she had picked up the oranges in her hand as fast as she could. They were all full of juice. With the mask on, what's the line she can't say? Is that enough to hide vulnerability? Like the "dusk is late night" , "less hardship, no fear today, " such lines, she went out in front of the mirror silently read, but now it is a sonorous towards me, grabbed me, melt uneasy. But inadvertently, already from the old man to hold hold the concentration of the orange to catch a secret word into the pocket, encourage their own step.

With the price tag on, the old man pushed away all kinds of fruits and vegetables, different brands of rice flour oil, and went straight to the plate of eggs. The road was clear. I exchanged glances with the meter reader and put a price tag on the tomato. Whisper thank you, he did not hear, but stretched out his hand, also "tomorrow will be better" the secret word to him.

Old People always look at the fate, epiphany with time layer upon layer, layer upon layer of light and dense, can not be said with others. But the disease had to cut open the heart with a knife to prove the depth of this great enlightenment, and the city's elderly were not stingy with wisdom. Running around the supermarket, it's their front line against the plague, the sweet salt that guards the town. It was a romantic moment in a small town, and early in the morning the idea of making the best of a bad situation arose.

What was your city like before the outbreak in 50 words?

Recorded by: Rabbit Rain
COORDINATES: Baise, Guangxi
I live in a small city on the 18th line of China's southwest frontier, with Southeast Asian characteristics. The mountainous region is close to the Tropic of Cancer, and most of the locals are lean, dark and yellow. During the outbreak, the temperature in the small town continued to drop, people put on heavy cotton clothes, put on white masks, due to the few confirmed cases, people look like heart fat, skin color with mask light, white several degrees.
Reporter: Song Rui
Coordinates: Ensch, Hubei
As a tourist city, it is normal to be noisy and noisy day and night. In addition to the ever crowded scenic spot, the bean skin shop and slag shop roadside food stalls and Tujia restaurant are the main force, and when night falls, massage parlors light up red and green signs, the streets and alleys are always a battlefield for businessmen. Every time we go home, we will go to eat bean skin too early, the same day cooked bean skin smooth, green pepper with just out of the WOK of gas, add a little hot oil is the perfect breakfast, eat go out to meet acquaintances again.
